Eskom's Jan Oberholzer has more. DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has announced stage two load-shedding for Friday, starting at 9am. The embattled power utility says the load-shedding will last until at least 6am on Saturday. WATCH: Eskom: Pay up or face dark Christmas Eskom terminated its stage 2 rotational load-shedding at 5am Friday morning, 6 hours after the initial planned outage time. Eskom says this is due to unplanned breakdowns and low water levels at its pumped storage schemes among other issues. READ: Eskom: Pay up or face dark Christmas It says the outages are part of efforts to protect its power system from a total collapse. Consumers have been urged to check their load shedding schedules on the Eskom or municipal websites.